==English==

===Etymology===
Greek: ''syno-'' 'same', ''aesthesia'' 'sensation'

===Alternative spellings===
* ''(US)'' synesthesia

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}

# A [[physiological]] [[phenomenon]] whereby a particular [[sensory]] [[stimulus]] triggers a second [[sensation]].
#: Eg. Tasting sweetness may trigger the visual sensation of redness.